The first, Supplementary Information (SI) Table 1, presents the different archaeological contexts and their associated radiocarbon ages analyzed in the various age model structures that make up this analysis along with the various unmodeled and modeled chronological intervals associated with individual event dates (radiocarbon measurements) and archaeological cultures. The second table, entitled Table 3, presents the Highest Posterior Density (HPD) modeled intervals for the various archaeological (typo-technocomplexes) that make up the cultural phase portion of the intersecting phase model structures employed.
